loomCode:
phase "About This Project" "This project demonstrates **human-in-the-loop** review: the AI analyzes a support ticket, then pauses for a human to review and approve or reject the response.\n\n**How it works:**\n1. An LLM analyzes the customer's support request (summary, category, urgency, draft reply)\n2. A **Human node** pauses execution and sends a review form to the WeaveMind browser extension\n3. You review the AI's work, edit the draft if needed, and approve or reject\n4. A **Gate node** routes the result: approved responses go one way, rejections another\n\n**Setup:** Install the WeaveMind browser extension, create an API token in your dashboard, and paste it into the extension settings. When you run this project, the extension will show a pending task." {
  field llm_config apiKey label:"API Key" description:"Your OpenRouter API key for the LLM. Leave empty to use platform Credits."
}

phase "Scenario" "Edit these to try different support scenarios." {
  field user_name value label:"Customer Name" description:"The customer submitting the support request."
  field user_request value label:"Support Request" description:"The customer's message. Try different scenarios: refunds, technical issues, billing questions."
}

phase "AI Configuration" "Tune how the AI analyzes tickets." {
  field llm_config model label:"Model" description:"Which LLM to use for ticket analysis."
  field llm_config temperature label:"Temperature" description:"Lower = more consistent analysis, higher = more creative responses."
}

output approved_output data label:"Approved Response" description:"The final response text if the reviewer approved it."
output rejected_output data label:"Rejection Notes" description:"The reviewer's notes explaining why the ticket was rejected."
output metadata_output data label:"Review Metadata" description:"Reviewer notes and any priority override."
